text: Ossiculum is a monotypic plant genus in the family Orchidaceae. The sole species is Ossiculum aurantiacum. It is endemic to Cameroon. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests. It is threatened by habitat loss. ==References== Category:Angraecinae Category:Endemic orchids of Cameroon Category:Monotypic Epidendroideae genera Category:Vandeae genera Category:Critically endangered plants Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
